HEADWORD: Boyer
<hw>Boy"er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>boeijer</ets>; -- so called because these vessels were employed for
laying the <ets>boeijen</ets>, or buoys: cf. F. <ets>boyer</ets>. See
<er>Buoy</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A Flemish sloop with a
castle at each end.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Raleigh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

